# $project_name

Home Assistant automations built on the [Maestro framework](https://github.com/papa-marsh/hass-maestro).

## Setup

1. Fill in `HOME_ASSISTANT_URL` and `HOME_ASSISTANT_TOKEN` in `.env`. Create a long-lived access token at `<your-hass-url>/profile/security`.
2. Install dependencies: `uv sync`
3. Run the example test: `uv run pytest`
4. Deploy the stack (app + redis + postgres): `docker compose up -d --build` (or `just deploy`)

On first run against a live Home Assistant instance, the entity registry generates automatically into `registry/` as entity state changes arrive (`AUTOPOPULATE_REGISTRY=True`). Once populated, import your entities with full autocomplete:

```python
from registry import light, switch, sensor
```

## Project Layout

```
app.py             # Entrypoint: constructs MaestroApp from env vars; served by gunicorn
scripts/           # Your automation modules, auto-imported at startup
registry/          # Generated entity registry (gitignored)
custom_domains/    # Optional Entity subclass extensions
```

## Everyday Commands

```bash
uv run pytest              # Run tests
uv run ruff check .        # Lint
uv run ruff format .       # Format
uv run mypy .              # Type check

just deploy                # Rebuild and restart the Docker stack
just logs                  # Tail app logs
just shell                 # Flask shell with pre-loaded imports
just upgrade-maestro       # Update the pinned hass-maestro version and redeploy
```

## Learn More

The [framework README](https://github.com/papa-marsh/hass-maestro#readme) covers all trigger types, entity methods, push notifications, job scheduling, database models, and the testing framework.
